HEADWORD: Myohaematin
<hw>My`o*haem"a*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Myo-</ets> + <ets>haematin</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A red-colored respiratory pigment found
associated with hemoglobin in the muscle tissue of a large number of
animals, both vertebrate and invertebrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myoid</ent>⟦br⟧
